<item>
            <title>[SOLR-3629] core `config` attribute not persisted properly</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-3629</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If a custom config filename is set CoreContainer persists it as `conf` but attempts to read it as `config`.  This results in an exception saying that solrconfig.xml cannot be found--as it has reverted to searching for the default.  The work-around is to not set a custom config filename.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I noticed this both in trunk and branch_4x on the GitHub mirror.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
